general.description:
Simon has broad experience in private and public M&A, equity capital markets and general corporate advisory work in both Australia and the UK. Simon has advised in connection with takeovers, schemes of arrangement and private M&A transactions. He has also advised on a number of fundraisings including IPOs, rights issues and placements acting for both issuers and underwriters.

Simon spent 4 years working in London where he advised corporates and investment banks including, among others, advising the underwriters on the US$15.2 billion rights issue by Rio Tinto plc and Rio Tinto Limited (the first ever rights issue by a DLC) and advising Lonmin plc on its successful defence of a £5.6 billion takeover by Xstrata plc.

Simon has worked on a number of significant transactions, both public and private including:

*  Galaxy Resources on the announced sale of 100% of Galaxy Resources' Jiangsu Lithium Carbonate Plant in China to Sichuan Tianqi Lithium Industries Inc for US$122 million, representing an enterprise value of US$230 million;
* Delta Resource Management and Michael Fotios on the restructure of Investmet via a $34 million in specie selective buy-back;
* Perpetual Mining in relation to a $52.3 million investment in Mindax Limited’s Mt Forrest Iron Project;
• Galaxy Resources on its $36m capital raising and financing transactions focussed on re-structuring the company's balance sheet;
* West African Resources on its Merger with Channel Resources Limited;
* Wolf Petroleum on the $40 million takeover bid by Strzelecki Metals;
* Phillips River Mining on the bid by Silver Lake Resources and the subsequent asset sale to Silver Lake for approximately $20 million;
* Perilya on its A$110.5 million accelerated non renounceable rights issue;
* Adamus Resources on its A$600 million merger of equals with TSX listed Endeavour Mining.

